Giro Velogames Daily Update

Race Results - Stage 21




Many of you no doubt already know the result, but heres the non-spoiler 5min highlight clip on Youtube:

https://youtu.be/iBVVAbSllJk





Although Time Trial specialist Tom Dumoulin was pipped by countryman Jos van Emden for victory in the final stage of the Giro DItalia, the Dutchman was most interested in the finishing time of the little Columbian and wearer of the leaders Maglia Rosa, the last rider to finish. Big Tom need not be concerned as his time gap over Quintana was more than enough to secure his first Grand Tour win. Duloulins victory in the 100th edition of the Giro was historic for more than one reason, given its the first Grand Tour victory for a Dutch rider since Joop Zoetemelk won the 1980 Tour de France.

Nairo Quintana limited his time loss to finish second overall with last years winner Vincenzo Nibali claiming the final spot on the podium.

Velogames Results - Cunning Stunts - Final


Its worth pointing out the method used by Velogames for calculating points after the final stage. Velogames awards points in the normal manner for Stage 21, but then awards points using an imaginary Stage 22 for Bonus Points based on rider finishing positions in accordance with the game rules:

https://www.velogames.com/giro-ditalia/2017/scores.php
